20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-61-1752055263.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22One%20of%20the%20core%20principles%20of%20%E2%80%98The%20Kindness%20Meal%E2%80%99%20is%20generational%20sharing%2C%20where%20older%20generations%20pass%20down%20their%20knowledge%20of%20food%20and%20recipes%20to%20younger%20people.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-61-1752055263.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-61-1752055263-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-61-1752055263-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-61-1752055263-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-61-1752055263-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-466523%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cem%3EOne%20of%20the%20core%20principles%20of%20%E2%80%98The%20Kindness%20Meal%E2%80%99%20is%20generational%20sharing.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecalling%20an%20experience%20working%20with%20a%20weaving%20cluster%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20used%20to%20have%20our%20meals%20at%20different%20homes%20each%20day.%20However%2C%20one%20particularly%20hot%20summer%20day%2C%20I%20developed%20a%20headache%20and%20lost%20my%20appetite.%20I%20declined%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ealoo%20chole%20puri%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0that%20was%20prepared%20for%20me%20and%20instead%20requested%20the%20same%C2%A0%3Cem%3Echaas%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eroti%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0that%20her%20son%20was%20eating.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3Cem%3EChaas%20roti%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eor%20simply%20buttermilk%20and%20chapati%20is%20often%20made%20during%20the%20summers%20when%20it%20gets%20too%20hot%20to%20cook%20on%20an%20open%20fire%20mud%20stove.%20The%20dish%20is%20simple%2C%20made%20with%20leftover%20dried%20chapati%20bites%20crushed%20into%20a%20bowl%20of%20cold%20buttermilk%20with%20onions%2C%20mint%2C%20green%20chillies%20and%20salt.%20It%20is%20a%20naturally%20cooling%20recipe%20that%20protects%20from%20the%20strong%20gusts%20of%20loo.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20she%20said%20it%20in%20front%20of%20her%20son%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20something%20I%20would%20like%20because%20it%20is%20the%20food%20of%C2%A0%3Cem%3Edehati%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20derogatory%20term%20for%20villagers).%20I%20think%20that%E2%80%99s%20one%20incident%2C%20I%20can%20never%20take%20out%20of%20my%20head%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dipali%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20any%20urban-looking%20person%20asks%20them%20for%20local%20food%2C%20they%E2%80%99ll%20end%20up%20making%C2%A0%3Cem%3Edaal%20bati%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(Lentil%20and%20wheat%20bread%20balls)%2C%20thinking%20that%E2%80%99s%20all%20we%20have%20the%20taste%20for%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20reflects.%20The%20pressure%20to%20conform%20to%20urban%20food%20preferences%20and%20the%20commercialisation%20of%20local%20food%20culture%20was%20evident.%20But%20the%20irony%2C%20as%20Dipali%20found%2C%20was%20that%20these%20people%20were%20sitting%20on%20a%20treasure%20trove%20of%20unique%2C%20locally%20grown%2C%20and%20indigenous%20foods%20%E2%80%94%20foods%20that%20were%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20being%20lost%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20Dipali%E2%80%99s%20journey%20began%20as%20a%20personal%20quest%20to%20understand%20her%20roots.%20This%20led%20her%20to%20embark%20on%20in-depth%20research%2C%20exploring%20the%20remote%20corners%20of%20Rajasthan.%20She%20meticulously%20documented%20local%20eating%20habits%2C%20indigenous%20ingredients%2C%20their%20seasonal%20availability%2C%20storage%20techniques%2C%20and%20the%20diverse%20recipes%20they%20inspired.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20broadly%20identifies%20nine%20cultural%20zones%20in%20Rajasthan%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20geography%2C%20the%20agricultural%20features%2C%20and%20language.%20Due%20to%20its%20location%2C%20Marwar%2C%20or%20the%20desert%20region%20of%20Rajasthan%2C%20has%20always%20depended%20on%20forged%20ingredients%20instead%20of%20greens.%20Ingredients%20like%3Cem%3E%C2%A0pholga%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eor%C2%A0%3Cem%3Efogla%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(Cooling%20food)%3Cem%3E%2C%20ber%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(Rajasthani%20Plum)%3Cem%3E%2C%20ker%20shangri%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(Caper%20berry)%20are%20commonly%20consumed.%20Most%20of%20the%20Rajasthani%20food%20served%20around%20the%20country%20like%C2%A0%3Cem%3Elaal%20maas%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(Red%20Meat%20Curry)%3Cem%3E%2C%20daal%20bati%2C%20ker%20shangri%20ki%20sabzi%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(Caper%20berry%20curry)%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eall%20come%20from%20these%20regions.%20But%20what%20about%20the%20rest%20of%20it%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20Bagad%20region%20which%20comprises%20Hunumangarh%20and%20Ganganagar%2C%20is%20also%20known%20as%20the%20Punjab%20of%20Rajasthan%2C%20because%20of%20its%20lush%20and%20fertile%20lands.%20Their%20eating%20habits%20are%20very%20different%20from%20Marwar.%20The%20Chambal%20river%20flows%20in%20the%20Mewar%20region%2C%20and%20because%20of%20the%20availability%20of%20fresh%20water%2C%20they%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20dishes%20that%20include%20fish.%20But%20because%20it%20does%20not%20fit%20into%20the%20homogenous%20idea%20of%20Rajasthan%2C%20all%20this%20is%20often%20excluded.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20her%20curated%20dining%20experiences%20and%20pop-up%20events%2C%20Dipali%20brings%20out%20these%20underrated%20aspects%20of%20Rajasthani%20cuisine.%20She%20introduces%20these%20dishes%20to%20a%20wider%20audience%20and%20helps%20them%20develop%20a%20deeper%20connection%20to%20the%20food%20they%E2%80%99re%20enjoying%20by%20giving%20them%20a%20thorough%20understanding%20of%20its%20origins%20and%20cultural%20significance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EEncouraging%20children%20to%20document%20their%20family%20recipes%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20core%20principles%20of%20%E2%80%98The%20Kindness%20Meal%E2%80%99%20is%20generational%20sharing%2C%20where%20older%20generations%20pass%20down%20their%20knowledge%20of%20food%20and%20recipes%20to%20younger%20people.%20This%20is%20crucial%20in%20a%20time%20when%20traditional%20recipes%20are%20being%20lost%20due%20to%20the%20changing%20dynamics%20of%20family%20structures%20and%20lifestyles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20organise%20%E2%80%98Food%20Culture%20Play%20Dates%E2%80%99%20for%20children%20aged%20between%20seven%20and%2014%2C%20which%20aims%20to%20teach%20children%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20food%20in%20their%20cultural%20heritage.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20train%20the%20kids%20to%20be%20ethnographic%20and%20document%20their%20family%20recipes%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dipali%20explains.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20also%20creates%20this%20sense%20of%20wonder%20%E2%80%94%20what%20was%20the%20food%2C%20and%20where%20is%20it%20coming%20from%3F%20And%20makes%20you%20want%20to%20know%20more.%E2%80%9D%20The%20children%20are%20encouraged%20to%20speak%20to%20their%20family%20members%20about%20the%20food%20they%20ate%20growing%20up%20and%20the%20stories%20around%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-62-1752055399.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22She%20broadly%20identifies%20nine%20cultural%20zones%20in%20Rajasthan%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20geography%2C%20the%20agricultural%20features%2C%20and%20language.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-62-1752055399.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-62-1752055399-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-62-1752055399-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-62-1752055399-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-62-1752055399-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-466528%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EShe%20broadly%20identifies%20nine%20cultural%20zones%20in%20Rajasthan%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20geography%2C%20the%20agricultural%20features%2C%20and%20language%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDipali%20recalls%20a%20heartwarming%20tale%20from%20one%20of%20their%20sessions%2C%20where%20a%20child%20shared%20her%20father%E2%80%99s%20family%E2%80%99s%20tradition%20of%20drinking%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ejadi%20ber%20ki%20chai%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20tea%20made%20from%20the%20dried%20fruit%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eber%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Etree%2C%20to%20help%20her%20grandmother%20with%20insomnia.%20The%20child%E2%80%99s%20father%20was%20incredibly%20moved%20by%20the%20memory%2C%20as%20he%20realised%20how%20important%20this%20family%20ritual%20had%20been%2C%20and%20how%20it%20had%20slipped%20away%20when%20the%20family%20moved%20to%20Jaipur.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESanjana%20Sarkar%2C%2038%2C%20who%20works%20with%20the%20French%20Embassy%20and%20serves%20as%20the%20director%20of%20Alliance%20Fran%C3%A7aise%2C%20Jaipur%2C%20describes%20herself%20as%20someone%20who%20%E2%80%9Clives%20to%20eat%E2%80%9D.%20During%20one%20of%20the%20Food%20Culture%20Play%20Dates%2C%20children%20from%20various%20schools%2C%20diverse%20in%20terms%20of%20financial%20backgrounds%2C%20came%20together.%20%E2%80%9COn%20the%20first%20day%2C%20we%20noticed%20that%20when%20asked%20about%20what%20type%20of%20food%20they%20like%2C%20they%20all%20had%20a%20common%20preference%20for%20processed%20and%20packaged%20foods%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls%3B%20%E2%80%9CBut%20the%20next%20day%2C%20when%20they%20came%20with%20their%20stories%20about%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eber%20ki%20chai%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(Rajasthani%20plum%20tea)%20and%C2%A0%3Cem%3Elehsun%20ki%20kheer%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(Garlic%20rice%20pudding)%2C%20the%20curiosity%20was%20palpable.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20two%20day%20workshop%2C%20they%20made%20a%20binder%20with%20all%20the%20traditional%20recipes%20shared%20by%20the%20children.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20binder%20is%20kept%20in%20our%20library%20here%2C%20and%20we%E2%80%99ve%20archived%20those%20recipes%20to%20do%20our%20part%20in%20preserving%20this%20rich%20food%20heritage%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20want%20to%20encourage%20children%20to%20enjoy%20their%20own%20home%2C%20community%2C%20or%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F382249%2Fbest-khau-gallis-food-walks-tours-trails-mysuru-mumbai-delhi-kolkata-varanasi-northeast%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estate%E2%80%99s%20food%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20champion%20it%20before%20it%20all%20begins%20to%20look%20and%20taste%20the%20same.%E2%80%9D%20By%20documenting%20and%20sharing%20these%20recipes%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20Kindness%20Meal%E2%80%99%20is%20helping%20future%20generations%20not%20lose%20touch%20with%20their%20culinary%20heritage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHelping%20people%20connect%20to%20their%20roots%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManohar%20Kabeer%20(32)%2C%20a%20communications%20professional%2C%20found%20out%20about%20%E2%80%98The%20Kindness%20Meal%E2%80%99%20when%20a%20friend%20shared%20a%20reel%20of%20theirs.%20%E2%80%9CI%20felt%20as%20though%20I%20was%20the%20beneficiary%20of%20what%20she%20was%20trying%20to%20do%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%20A%20Rajasthani%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20Maharashtra%2C%20Manohar%20was%20taken%20back%20to%20summers%20in%20his%C2%A0%3Cem%3Enani%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(grandmother)%20house.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20would%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20dishes%20made%20with%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ebajra%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(pearl%20millets)%2C%20I%20especially%20remember%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3Erabdi%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20thickened%2C%20sweetened%20milk%20dish).%20Then%20there%20were%20foraged%20foods%20like%C2%A0%3Cem%3Emangodi%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20variation%20of%20the%20mung%20bean)%2C%20and%C2%A0%3Cem%3Esangri%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(desert%20bean)%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20would%20be%20used%20to%20make%20sabzi%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-63-1752055497.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22By%20documenting%20and%20sharing%20these%20recipes%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20Kindness%20Meal%E2%80%99%20is%20helping%20future%20generations%20not%20lose%20touch%20with%20their%20culinary%20heritage..%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-63-1752055497.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-63-1752055497-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-63-1752055497-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-63-1752055497-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-63-1752055497-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-466531%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-ca